Thousands of police officers seeking treatment have been turned away from hospitals around the country following after a miscommunication between the agencies.According to a memo from Kenya Police Service headquarters to all Regional Coordinators, Formation commanders, County Commanders and Police headquarters directorates, police officers are encountering difficulties accessing services at various medical facilities.Inspector General of Police Joseph Boinett yesterday confirmed that police are transitioning from an old system to the new one which began one month ago.He said the consortium started registering members digitally sixteen days ago.